CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 5, 1958, pg. A3, reads: "Christening Party - Some of the guests who participated in rites giving Christian baptism to little Charlene Marietta Foggie, Sunday morning, where caught by The Courier photographer following a fete at the Tubman Terrace House. Left to right: Mrs. Abbie C. Jackson, Louisville, Ky; Mrs. C. H. Foggie and the Rev. Charles H. Foggie, parents of the child; Mrs. Helen Dougan, the Rev. James A. Clement holding his god-child; Mrs. Martin L. Harvey, Baton Rouge, La., and Mary Elizabeth Clement in the foreground. - Harris Photo.:
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Abby Clement or Abbie Jackson, Madeline Sharpe Foggie, Rev. Charles H. Foggie, Helen Sharpe Dougan, Rev. Harvey or Rev. James A. Clement holding baby Charlene Foggie, Claire Harvey, and Mary Elizabeth Clement, posed outdoors for baptism of Charlene Foggie
